It's the roleplay!!!  Plus that nice Disease Cloud symbol!<br>
<br>
Clerics have one fighting advantage over all other classes--undead.  The trouble with most undead creatures is that you get mostly bone chips off of <br>
them.  Are there any undead that loot GOOD items?<br>
<br>
(The best I've ever seen was when my former Bard,<br>
Chorine, was given a 10pp scythe from a 34 spectre.)<br>
<br>
So what are the undead carrying around that's decent?<br>
<br>
Thank ye!<br>
Rhaxalygen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tinwinsilvertick>Tinwin Silvertick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/14/03 12:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4475.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Loot and Undead</span><hr size=1> ((Get yourself up to level 20 or so and you will find nice loots on the undead of Unrest (Unrest is tricky to get to know, but once learned, you can rule it. Great loot and a big exp bonus there). You'll find that undead usually have pretty nice loot beyond that level. You can gain exp in Unrest till your high 40s actually <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  though around level 35 you can go and solo ghouls in lower Guk for nice profit, but at that level there are quite a few other places to choose from too.))<br>
