<br>
Just be polite but firm that you deserve a fair share even though you are spending most of your time medding so that you can heal them.  If they are incapable of dealing with that, move on and find another group.  As a bonus you may find people that are also interested in having good group dynamics and want to work well together and kick butt.  These are the people you can trust to group with for the next 50 levels after that...which is probably much more valuable than any loot you will ever get at these levels.<br>
<br>
If you are a person who mostly wants to solo, not sure cleric is an efficient choice...a druid would probably be better and have almost as much healing power (ducks stones thrown by irate clerics) or if you want to solo undead, maybe a paladin/SK/Necro.  No matter what choices you make, the best of luck to you.<br>
<br>
